title: Genie, Make a Wish
synopsis: Jinn, a genie who awakens after a thousand years, and Ka-young, his new impassive master.

title: The Glory

title: The Frog
synopsis: A man's life unravels when a mysterious woman arrives at his motel one summer, forcing him to grasp tightly to what he cherishes most.

writer: ['J.Q. Lee', 'Oh Bo-hyun', 'Da Hee Kim', 'Nam-su Kim', 'Lee Nam-Gyoo']

title: Hierarchy

title: Extracurricular

title: The Witch

writer: ['Kim Jae-eun', 'Kang Je-kyu', 'Kyu Won Jo', 'Hyun Joon Kim']

title: Because This Is My First Life
synopsis: Ji Ho is a single woman. She's a writing assistant of dramas. She's a strong and determined woman. Unfortunately, she has to leave her house and seeks other place to live. Her friends help her to find a roommate. That roommate is Se Hee.

synopsis: During a time of chaos, a judge turns the court into something like a reality show and punishes evil people mercilessly.

title: Uncontrollably Fond
synopsis: The memory of their painful breakup still fresh in their minds, two former lovers reunite years later as a top actor and a documentary producer.

title: Red Sleeve
synopsis: Based on a novel of the same name, it tells the record of a royal court romance between the King of Joseon who places his duty to his country first above love, and a court lady who wants to protect the life she has chosen.

synopsis: A former troublemaker applies for a job at a convenience store owned by the same man who ran errands for her a few years ago.

title: Law and the City
synopsis: Five attorneys at a law firm navigate cases and build friendships. They include An Ju Hyeong, a competent but detached senior lawyer, and Kang Hui Ji, a passionate junior associate who believes in changing lives.

title: Tomorrow

synopsis: A work dealing with buying abandoned children by their parents and selling them based on price and rating, as well as the illegal adoption cartel that provides a free refund service if you do not like the child while raising it.

synopsis: Follows the story of Ok Chan-mi as she seeks revenge for the death of her twin brother.

synopsis: A disgraced former rugby star returns as a coach to his high school's struggling team, where he reunites with his ex-girlfriend and helps the determined captain lead the team to redemption.

title: Heirs
synopsis: After a chance encounter in LA, two teens from different social backgrounds reunite at an exclusive high school attended by Korea's über rich.

title: Physical: 100
synopsis: One hundred contestants in top physical shape compete in a series of grueling challenges to claim the honor - and cash reward - as the last one standing.

title: First Lady
synopsis: Just two months before the president-elect is sworn in, he demands a divorce from his wife - but she dreamed of becoming the first lady.

title: Romance Is a Bonus Book
synopsis: A gifted writer who's the youngest editor-in-chief ever at his publishing company gets enmeshed in the life of a former copywriter desperate for a job.

title: Suspicious Partner
synopsis: A young woman grows close to a prosecutor as she works with him as a trainee in a murder case. However, things take a turn when she inexplicably becomes a suspect.

title: Love in the Moonlight
synopsis: The unlikely love story between a crown prince and his eunuch.

title: Island
synopsis: Won Mi Ho's arrogant and selfish attitude causes her father banishing her to Jeju island. Unbeknownst to her, the island is where evil roams free.

title: Dynamite Kiss
synopsis: A single woman who disguises herself as a married mom to get a job, and the team leader of a baby products company who falls in love with her.

title: Sisyphus: The Myth
synopsis: An unfathomable incident introduces a genius engineer to dangerous secrets of the world, and to a woman from the future who's come looking for him.

title: The Veil
synopsis: A spy investigation show with a story about a top National Intelligence Service (NIS) agent. In his endeavor to uncover the internal traitor that brought him to his downfall, he confronts a much bigger enemy behind the organization.

title: The Judge from Hell
synopsis: Kang Bit Na, an elite judge with a beautiful appearance, is a demon whose mission is to punish those who have wronged others and send them to Hell. However, the righteous Detective Han Da On is determined to change her ways.

title: Record of Youth
synopsis: Two actors and a makeup artist fight to make their own way in a world that weighs the backgrounds they were born into more than their dreams.

title: Shin's Project
synopsis: CEO Sin is a character who runs a fried chicken restaurant in a small town while keeping a secret hidden behind a veil and clashes with villains with his 'verbal skills' and body.

title: Noblewoman
synopsis: Born to a single mom working as a maid, Shin Ae gives up her studies to work as a salesperson in a department store. Mi Na is the only daughter and heiress of the family who owns the department store and secretly envies Shin Ae for her inborn confidence. Shin Ae has a crush on Jung Min, a manager at the store she works in. Smart and capable, Jung Min is involved in a secret relationship with Mi Na. However, Mi Na's parents disapprove of Jung Min's ordinary background. When Shin Ae finds out that Jung Min and Mi Na are a couple, she is greatly disappointed. This is when a clumsy but lovable young man named Yeong Min meets Shin Ae. The two find comfort in each other and end up getting married. However, their happiness is cut short when Yeong Min and his parents die in a plane crash. Shin Ae is devastated by the sudden loss in the early days of her marriage. However, there is an unexpected twist, Yeong Min's father had actually been a huge investor and major shareholder in the department store. Shin Ae inherits the wealth that she had always dreamed of. Shin Ae, who had only been able to dream about becoming rich, is now indisputably part of the upper class. Her changed status does not bring her true happiness. Unable to accept that Shin Ae has risen to her status, Mi Na hatches a scheme against her, creating conflict and conspiracy over the ownership of the department store. Meanwhile, Shin Ae continues to have feelings for Jung Min. This drama is an epic tale of love and competition between two high school classmates from completely different worlds, each trying to become a truly noble lady.

title: Save Me
synopsis: A young girl coming to a small town with her family. And through tragic events getting involved with a religious cult.

title: Love, Take Two
synopsis: A 43-year-old single mom and her 23-year-old, medical student daughter starting a new chapter in their lives by heading off to the countryside, encountering people along the way who teach them meaningful lessons about life.

title: Run On
synopsis: Veering off course from his preset path, a track star follows his own pace and heart for the first time after a film translator steps into his life

title: Extraordinary You
synopsis: The story of a girl who finds out that she is in fact a supporting character in a web comic and decides to change her fate.

title: Youth of May
synopsis: In May, 1980, during the turbulent times of the Gwangju Uprising, Hee-Tae and Myung-Hee fall in love. Their love seems destined by fate.

title: The Echoes of Survivors: Inside Korea's Tragedies
synopsis: Showcases the tales of those who survived Korea's darkest chapters, shining a light on hidden truths.

title: Jirisan
synopsis: Set against the backdrop of towering views of Mount Jiri, it depicts the story of rangers and other employees of the Jirisan National Park who climb through the mysterious and unexplored regions of the mountain.

title: Doom at Your Service
synopsis: Tak Dong Kyung lives a fairly ordinary life until she stumbles into an unexpected fate and ends up signing a hundred-day contract with Myul Mang, risking her everything.

title: Perfect Marriage Revenge
synopsis: The story of Han Yi-joo, who chose a contract marriage to avenge her husband and family, and Seo Do-gook who postpones a contract marriage to welcome her as his wife.

title: Blood Free
synopsis: After millions of years, humans consuming animal meat, BF now dominates the market for genetically engineered cultured meat. There are people inside and outside BF who starting to have doubts about the path taken by BF's CEO.

title: Crash Course in Romance
synopsis: Retired national team female handball player has become a Banchan take-out store owner in order to look after her family while she grapples with her daughter's tutor's many quirks.

title: Reborn Rich
synopsis: After ten years, a loyal employee is framed for embezzlement, then murdered by his employers, only to be reborn as their youngest son with a yearning for revenge guiding his hostile takeover.

title: Prison Playbook
synopsis: Baseball pitcher Kim Je-hyeok becomes a convict overnight after being sent to prison for defending his sister from a sexual assault, days before he was due to fly to the US to join the Boston Red Sox.

title: Welcome to Waikiki
synopsis: With big dreams of financing their own film project, three struggling young men join forces in a guesthouse venture that is anything but profitable.

title: Heartbeat
synopsis: A romance drama about a semi-human vampire named Seon Woo-hyeol, who failed to become a human by a day out of 100 years, and a woman Joo In-hae, who doesn't have a single human decency, starting to live together and finding true warmth.

title: Wedding Impossible
synopsis: Na Ah Jeong enters a contractual marriage with her friend Lee Do Han, heir to the chaebol LJ Group, to conceal a secret from his family. Complications arise when Do Han's brother Lee Ji Han opposes their arrangement.

title: Glitch
synopsis: Hong Ji Hyo's boyfriend disappears with an unidentified light. Since then, Hong Ji Hyo traces her boyfriend's whereabouts. With the help of a UFO club members, she approaches a mysterious secret.

title: Friendly Rivalry
synopsis: A gripping teen mystery thriller that centers on the intense bond between teenage girls as they navigate a brutal survival competition even more challenging than the entrance exam.

title: The First Responders
synopsis: An action drama about first responders involving the police and firefighters who work together in emergency situations to fight against crime and fire.

title: Parasyte: The Grey
synopsis: A group of humans wage war against the rising evil of unidentified parasitic life-forms that live off of human hosts and strive to grow their power

title: Black Knight
synopsis: In 2071, toxic air pollution has devastated the world, leaving society reliant on drivers known as Knights for necessities. When a revered Knight meets a young refugee determined to join the ranks, he agrees to help him achieve his dream.

title: Hometown
synopsis: A mystery evil thriller which finds the truth of a recording tape containing mysterious serial killings and unidentified sounds in a small city.

title: Yumi's Cells
synopsis: The story of an ordinary office worker named Yumi-from the point of view of the many brain cells in her head controlling her every thought, feeling, and action.

title: A Good Day to Be a Dog
synopsis: An unpredictable fantasy romance between a woman living under a curse that causes her to turn into a dog when kissed, and the only one who can help her overcome the curse is a man who is afraid of dogs.

title: Return to the Palace
synopsis: The story takes place in the royal palace, where a conspiracy summons an evil spirit (Palcheokgwi) with a grudge against the royal family. A shaman fights against him initially to save her first love, alongside her spirit guardian.

title: Narco-Saints
synopsis: A civilian businessman who has no choice but to cooperate with the secret operation of the National Intelligence Service to arrest the Korean drug lord who has taken control of Suriname in South America.

title: Melloga Chejil
synopsis: A romantic comedy that depicts the daily lives of 30-year-old best friends Lim Jin Joo, Lee Eun Jung and Hwang Han Joo.

title: The Art of Negotiation
synopsis: A merger and acquisitions specialist, Yoon Joo-No, is a legendary negotiator. His team of experts including Lawyer Oh Soon-Young and Choi Jin-Soo specialize in large corporation deals between companies.

title: The World of the Married
synopsis: A story about a married couple whose betrayal of one another leads to a whirlwind of revenge.

title: Kiss Sixth Sense
synopsis: Ye Sol can see the future when she kisses someone. One day she accidentally kissed her boss Cha Min Hoo and saw that in the future they were lying in the same bed.

title: Crime Scene Zero
synopsis: Players take roles of detectives and suspects in this crime-solving game. With clues and wits, can they expose the culprit among them?

title: A Wonderful Sight
synopsis: A reclusive ex-cop reenters the game as an insurance investigator, searching for clues in crime scenes perfectly staged by a serial killer in her midst.

title: Those Who Read the Hearts of Evil
synopsis: A crime thriller drama based on a web novel of the same name that contains the field experience of Kwon Il Yong, Korea's No. 1 profiler.

title: Somebody
synopsis: When a software developer creates a dating app that a serial killer uses to find his next targets, she's drawn into a dark world of romance and murder.

title: Mad for Each Other
synopsis: Bothered to realize they are next-door neighbors and share a psychiatrist, a man and a woman find it's impossible to stay out of each other's way.

title: Family
synopsis: A spy comedy drama about an NIS Black agent husband disguised as an ordinary office worker and a sweet and cruel wife dreaming of a perfect family.

title: Can This Love Be Translated?
synopsis: A man with a job interpreting other languages meets a woman who speaks love in a completely opposite way to him and understands each other.

title: Tunnel
synopsis: A detective follows the trail of a serial killer 30 years into the future and teams up with detectives in that time period to find the culprit.

title: The Dream Life of Mr. Kim
synopsis: After 25 years of success at one company, Manager Kim loses his job and family, forcing him to redefine himself beyond his roles as corporate manager, husband, and father.

title: Live Up to Your Name
synopsis: The best acupuncturist of Joseon, Heo Im, finds himself traveling 400 years into the future, where he meets Choi Yeon Kyung, doctor in a modern hospital. Though impressed by her, differences in their methods and priorities make them clash.

title: Abyss
synopsis: After meeting an untimely demise in separate incidents, Cha Min and Go Se-yeon discover they've come back to life in new bodies they don't recognize.

title: Wonderful World
synopsis: Psychology professor and writer Eun Soo Hyun's world shatters when her son suffers an unpunished injustice. Seeking vengeance, she unexpectedly discovers solace helping others embroiled in comparable cryptic cases.

title: One Dollar Lawyer
synopsis: A story of a lawyer with unusual style who only charges 1,000 won (roughly 1 dollar) for his service to fight for clients that are up against the richest and most privileged.

title: When the Weather is Fine
synopsis: A story about forgiveness, healing and love taking place around a small book store in the countryside.

title: May I Help You
synopsis: Baek Dong-Joo works as a funeral director who has a supernatural power that allows her to see and talk to the dead.

title: The Fiery Priest
synopsis: A drama about a Catholic priest with anger management issues and a detective from the Gudam Police Station who meet during their joint investigation into the murder of an elderly priest.

title: My First First Love
synopsis: The story of college students and their realization of first love as they make new friends.

title: Brewing Love
synopsis: Chae Yong-Joo, a former special forces member and top salesperson at a liquor company, must sell a new beer to save her store from closing. She meets a sensitive brewmaster, Yoon Min-Joo, while competing with manager Bang A-Reum.

title: Pinocchio
synopsis: A young boy, whose life and family has been destroyed by new media, gets adopted by a family in a rural area after being found lost at sea. He conceals his past for 13 years. But then the girl he loves, a reporter, finds out the truth.

title: When the Camellia Blooms
synopsis: A love story of the single-parent Dongbaek, the owner of Camellia Bar among a small neighborhood, who is also being the next murder target of a serial killer case.

title: The Tale of Lady Ok
synopsis: Set in the Joseon period, Ok Tae-Young is an attorney with a secret identity. Her name, her husband, and her status are all fake. She meets Cheon Seung-Hwi, a traveling storyteller who falls in love with her at first sight.

title: Love Your Enemy
synopsis: Childhood enemies Seok Ji-won (man) and Yoon Ji-won (woman), born the same day with the same name, reunite 18 years later. Their families' rivalry fuels their clashes, making them troublemakers who fight at every chance.

title: Investigation Partners
synopsis: This show is about a brilliant forensic doctor and a rookie prosecutor who works together to solve cases.

title: Designated Survivor: 60 Days
synopsis: When the National Assembly suffers a catastrophic attack, Minister of Environment Park Mu Jin must find a way to lead Korea through the ensuing chaos.

title: Song of the Bandits
synopsis: The Koreans who gathered in Gando, Manchuria, for their own reasons and band together to protect their homes during 1910-45 Japanese colonial rule.

title: The First Night with the Duke
synopsis: College student K enters her favorite historical romance novel as noble's daughter Cha Seon Chaek. After one night with royal-blooded Lee Beon, she tries to pair him with the novel's heroine, but fate has other plans.

title: Bulgasal
synopsis: The story of a man-turned-immortal, Bulgasal, who wants revenge from a woman with a mysterious past and present, who he deems responsible for his immortality and miseries from the past 600 years, hoping to free himself from his curse.

title: Unmasked
synopsis: A team of investigative journalists tries to solve a twenty-year-old cold case involving a famous actor who went missing.

title: Pyramid Game
synopsis: Each person is graded through a popular vote against the backdrop of a girl's high school and if they receive an F grade, they become legitimate victims of school violence.

title: The Empress Ki
synopsis: A Korea-born warrior girl had to be a servant at the Mongol Yuan court but somehow overcame her low status to become an empress in another land.

title: Rookie Historian Goo Hae-Ryung
synopsis: Set in 19th-century Korea, a female historian faces gender discrimination but perseveres. She gets entangled with Prince Lee Rim, blurring lines between duty and personal involvement.

title: Jewel in the Palace
synopsis: A series based on a real person in Korean history, Suh, Jang-geum.

title: Age of Youth
synopsis: Five college students, from different walks of life end up living together in a fictional house share called Belle Epoque.

title: Connection
synopsis: A story that reveals the whole story of a friendship that has been changed over 20 years based on the death of a friend of Jang Jae-kyeong, an ace detective in a drug squad who is forcibly addicted to drugs.

title: Revenant
synopsis: Ku San Young works and studies at night to become a public officer. After receiving a relic from her dead father mysterious deaths take place around her, and she finds herself slowly changing.

title: The Heavenly Idol
synopsis: A fantasy-romance drama about an unknown idol, Woo Yeon-woo, whose body was possessed by Rembrary, the god of this world.

title: Full House
synopsis: In a bid to reacquire her childhood home, a free-spirited woman agrees to a sham-marriage with a selfish actor. Their daily lives are complicated by overlapping love triangles and comic misadventures.

title: Mischievous Kiss
synopsis: Fate brings polar opposite high school classmates (one obsessively attracted to the other, the other indifferent to all advances) to live under one roof. Is romance possible?

title: She Was Pretty
synopsis: When Ji Sung-Joon was young, he was ugly. As he grew up, he began to have an attractive appearance. When Kim Hye-Jin was young, she was pretty. As she grew up, she became ugly. Ji Sung-Joon tries to find his first love.

title: Hello Monster
synopsis: Briliant criminal psychologist tries to solve murder cases that seem to be linked to one another, and something triggers a memory he himself thought he'd lost forever.

title: As You Stood By
synopsis: Two women are driven to the brink, facing an inescapable reality that forces them to consider murder as their only way out.

title: Awaken
synopsis: It's a story about what happened in a village 28 years ago that relates to the string of murders that have been occurring in the present day.

title: A Model Family
synopsis: After unwittingly stealing money from a cartel, a cash-strapped professor finds the only way to save his broken family is by working as a drug courier.

title: Culinary Class Wars
synopsis: Pits 100 renowned chefs and undiscovered talents against each other in a culinary battle. Judged by the esteemed Paik Jong-won and Chef Anh Sung-jae, the show promises to showcase the ultimate clash of culinary skills and creativity.

title: I Hear Your Voice
synopsis: A sharp female lawyer with no filter teams up with a public defender and a high-school student with special gifts to bring down a killer with a personal vendetta.

title: Mad Dog
synopsis: After a plane crash took his family, an ex-cop forms an investigation team and meets a genius ex-con whose brother died, starting a rivalry and partnership.

title: Sell Your Haunted House
synopsis: Ji Ah, who has a tragic past, runs a realty business in which she exorcises evil spirits from properties. When she meets a conman In Beom with special psychic powers who may be able to help her understand her past, the two join forces.

title: Celebrity
synopsis: Fame. Money. Power. One young woman fights to become the next hottest celebrity in the glamorous yet scandalous world of influencers in Seoul.

title: Alien Stage
synopsis: Aliens run a brutal singing contest for abducted humans in their post-apocalyptic world. Season 50 promises the same drama and thrills. Contestants must perform well or face elimination.

title: Memorist
synopsis: Based on the hit webtoon of the same name, "Memorist" is a mystery thriller that tells the story of Dong Baek, a detective with supernatural powers.

title: Anna
synopsis: Woman's petty lie spins her life in an entirely unforeseen direction. She finds herself living someone else's life in this unpredictable tale.

title: Find Me in Your Memory
synopsis: A love story between a man who remembers every second of his life and a woman who forgot her painful past.

title: Hello, Me!
synopsis: Miserable and unsuccessful, a woman thinks she's lost all her spark, until one day, her spunky younger self appears in front of her demanding change.

title: My ID Is Gangnam Beauty
synopsis: Bullied for her looks, Mi-rae gets plastic surgery hoping for a better kind of life but faces new challenges in college. Based on a hit Korean webtoon.

title: One Spring Night
synopsis: A couple in their 30s has dated for many years. When they begin to discuss marriage, they begin to look upon their relationship in a different light.

title: Secret Garden
synopsis: Gil Ra-im is a tough stuntwoman with a soft heart. Kim Joo-won is a nit-picky CEO with a long list of complexes. Love-struck, Joo-won barges into Ra-im's life in all the wrong ways, trying to make sense of his illogical feelings.

title: 100 Days My Prince
synopsis: Upon losing his memory, a crown prince encounters a commoner's life and experiences unforgettable love as the husband to Joseon's oldest bachelorette.

title: Love Song for Illusion
synopsis: A fantasy historical drama romance that crosses between a man with two opposite personalities and a woman who loves him, fresh love and fierce obsession.

title: The Killer's Shopping List
synopsis: One day, a dead body is found at an apartment near the supermarket. Finding this murder odd, Dae-sung, his mother, and his girlfriend Ah-hee gather around to find the real murderer, starting by looking through the receipts of the market.

title: The Eighth Sense: The Series
synopsis: An enigmatic senior crosses paths with a lost freshman. As their relationship blooms, they're forced to confront their inner demons and embark on a journey of self-discovery.

title: The 1st Shop of Coffee Prince
synopsis: A tomboy, mistaken for a lad, maintains the deception for the sake of employment. The situation becomes complicated when her male boss begins to develop feelings for this "boy."

title: Hunter with a Scalpel
synopsis: Se-hyun, a genius forensic scientist who discovers traces of her father's killings while doing an autopsy, and goes on a hunt in order to hide the past that she wants to erase, before the police get to the truth first.

title: Cinderella and the Four Knights
synopsis: A young girl who lives with her cruel stepmother and sister, accidentally meets 3 young and rich cousins who live a luxury life in a big mansion and is hired by the boys grandpa to look after their bad behavior.

title: Top Management
synopsis: Storyline follows the development of a kpop group who got caught up in a scandal. With the help of their manager who can see brief glimpses of the future they have to face the war that the entertainment business is to not be forgotten.

title: Family Plan
synopsis: A story about a group of people with special abilities who disguise themselves as family members to survive and use unique methods to overcome the vicious criminals who threaten them.

title: Nine: Nine Time Travels
synopsis: A TV anchorman discovers that a mysterious bundle of incense has the power to send him back in time, where he has the opportunity to alter the past.

title: The Atypical Family
synopsis: Bok Gwi Joo's family has supernatural abilities. He can revisit happy past moments. Depression causes him to lose this power. His family also loses abilities due to modern issues. Do Da He joins their household, instigating change.

title: The Moon Flows Through the River
synopsis: It tells the story of the soul exchange between a prince who has lost his smile and a saddle-carrying merchant who has lost her memory.

title: Doctor Cha Jeong Suk
synopsis: It tells the story of a medical graduate turned housewife but decided to return to the medical field, and a doctor husband who maintains a perfect dual life. He is great at his job and he is also great at cheating on his wife.

title: The Penthouse: War in Life
synopsis: The story of a woman who strives to achieve her goal of entering high society by becoming the "queen" in the 100th floor penthouse in Gangnam, the pinnacle of success in her eyes.

title: Six Flying Dragons
synopsis: Story of the the foundation of the Joseon Dynasty in Korea and ambition, success and fall of several real and fictional characters.

title: Rookie Cops
synopsis: A story that captures the challenges, spirit and passion of youth as two students at the Korean National Police University study to become cops.

title: The Golden Spoon
synopsis: Seung Cheon gets his hands on a magical spoon that allows him to switch lives with his rich best friend. Now he has to decide which of his two possible futures is worth keeping.

title: Encounter
synopsis: Brought together by fate, a woman who seems to have everything and a young man who seems to have nothing decides to give up an ordinary life to be together.

title: Doctor John
synopsis: In a refreshing take on the genre, "Doctor John" will portray the doctors' search for the cause of their patients' mysterious pain as a thrilling chase, almost like a detective hunting down the perpetrator behind an unsolved crime.

title: Tell Me What You Saw
synopsis: An eccentric genius profiler works with a detective with photographic memory and a police chief to go after a serial killer who was thought to be dead.

title: Touch Your Heart
synopsis: An affair between a lawyer and a first-rate actress, whose life goes downhill after being involved in a scandal. She fakes her position to become the lawyer's secretary and star in a writer's drama.

title: The Tale of Nokdu
synopsis: During the Joseon period, a man named Jeon Nok-du disguises himself as a woman to escape into a village of widows. There, he meets Dong Dong-ju, a kisaeng trainee who is more fond of crafts than singing or dancing.

title: The Kingdom of the Winds
synopsis: Story of of king Daemusin, third ruler of Goguryeo and grandson of king Jumong.

title: Tempted
synopsis: Love is just a game for Chaebol heir who agrees to a petty bet with his friends to seduce a college student - until he starts to fall for her.

title: Ghost Doctor
synopsis: Cha Young Min is a genius doctor but arrogant and selfish. One day, he gets involved in an unexpected case; his spirit possesses another doctor's body. These two doctors are complete opposites, with personalities and medical abilities.

title: Connect
synopsis: A man is kidnapped and one of his is eyes removed by a gang of organs hunters and transplanted into a serial killer. The unwilling donor now has terrible visions as he witnesses terrifying attacks on the residents of Seoul.

title: Still 17
synopsis: After emerging from a thirteen-year coma, a woman tries to adjust to adult life and reconnect with the man she believes is responsible for her condition.

title: Summer Strike
synopsis: Adapted from a webtoon. A drama about voluntary unemployed Lee Yeo-reum and librarian Ahn Dae-beom, who declared a life strike, leaving a complex city and looking for themselves in a strange place.

title: Mask Girl
synopsis: An office worker who is insecure about her looks becomes a masked internet personality by night until a chain of ill-fated events overtakes her life.

title: She Would Never Know
synopsis: Based on a popular 2017 Web Novel of the same name, it tells the love story between a lovely "sunbae" and a bold "hoobae".

title: My Secret Terrius
synopsis: Go Ae Rin suddenly loses her husband. A mysterious man, Kim Bon, lives next door. Kim Bon is a legendary NIS agent. He helps Ae Rin uncover a conspiracy, which husband became involved with.

title: The Forbidden Marriage
synopsis: Ye So-rang, a fraudulent match-maker insisting she can summon the deceased crown princess, shows up to King Lee Heon who proclaimed a ban on marriage since he lost his wife 7 years ago.

title: Once Upon a Small Town
synopsis: A city veterinarian moves to the countryside where he meets a policewoman, a town insider with a friendly secret.

title: Last Summer
synopsis: Twin brothers Do Ha and Do Yeong split up after parents' divorce. Do Ha lives in US, visits Korea summers to see neighbor Ha Kyung, who secretly likes him. His return stirs up hidden feelings and secrets from the past.

title: Such a Close Traitor
synopsis: A family psychological thriller about a dilemma that Korea's best profiler experiences when he learns the secret of his daughter related to the murder crime he is investigating.

title: Are You Human Too?
synopsis: A young heir falls into a coma after being brutally assaulted. However, his mother is determined to keep him in the race for the family fortune and creates a robot to replace him.

title: The Great Queen Seondeok
synopsis: Story of Queen Seondeok who was born a princess, brought up among commoners and overcame many trials to become the ruler of Silla.

title: The Bequeathed
synopsis: A story in which ominous things continue and the secrets of the family are revealed as they suddenly inherit the family mountain from their uncle, whom they had forgotten.

title: The Smile Has Left Your Eyes
synopsis: A detective probes a death case, his sister gets involved with a suspect. He tries keeping them apart, suspecting danger, but she sympathizes with the man, straining the case's progression.

title: Misaeng
synopsis: This a Drama series about a group of co-workers in their twenties who started their job at a big multinational company. This is a story about their everyday life, about their journey each day at the office.

title: Bing-ui
synopsis: A reluctant clairvoyant joins forces with a brusque police detective hiding a soft heart to help him solve criminal cases using her psychic abilities.

title: Love Scout
synopsis: Yoo Eun-ho, a single dad armed with perfection, becomes the secretary of Kang Ji-yun, the CEO of a popular headhunter company, who doesn't do anything except work.

title: Gaus Electronics
synopsis: Marketing team members at Gaus Electronics multinational navigate corporate politics, interpersonal dynamics and life events while maintaining camaraderie.

title: Lawless Lawyer
synopsis: Sangpil had witnessed the death of his mother, a former human rights lawyer. Brought up by his gangster uncle, he became an unprecedented gangster lawyer to avenge his mother's death.

title: Angel's Last Mission: Love
synopsis: Dan is a care-free angel who always gets into trouble. In order to return to heaven, he is tasked with a mission to find true love for a cold and single-minded ballerina Lee Yun Seo, but ends up falling for her himself.

title: Tarot
synopsis: Seven spooky tales centered on a cursed tarot deck, each story following those afflicted by its malevolent power as the cards change hands, unleashing supernatural terrors upon the unsuspecting owners.

title: Familiar Wife
synopsis: A married couple suddenly finds themselves living entirely different lives after their fates magically change through an unexpected incident.

title: Tomorrow with You
synopsis: The drama tells the story of Yoo So-joon, who can travel through time by a subway. After seeing his future-self living miserably, Joon decides to marry Ma Rin in order to avoid that fate. As time passes, he learns to love her selflessly.

title: No Gain No Love
synopsis: Follows a woman who embarks on a journey of self-discovery and personal growth, navigating the complexities of life and relationships while pursuing her dreams.

title: Adult Trainee
synopsis: Three different coming-of-age stories from the point of view of the protagonists about how they deal with their realities in high school at the end of their teenage period as Gen Z.

title: My Sassy Girl
synopsis: A love story of a cold city scholar Gyun Woo (Joo Won), who's known as "Joseon's national treasure", and the sassy princess Hye Myung (Oh Yeon-Seo) in a Joseon Dynasty era.

title: Once Upon a Boyhood
synopsis: Byung Tae, a socially awkward teen bullied for most of his life, transfers to the countryside, hoping for a fresh start. Yet high jinks ensue when he is mistaken for the best fighter in school and must maintain the facade.

title: Black
synopsis: A man possessed by death. A woman who can see death. The earthly and the afterworld collide dangerously.

title: Personal Taste
synopsis: A straight-laced architect falls in love with a furniture designer while pretending to be gay.

title: To My Star
synopsis: After his career takes a turn for the worse, superstar actor Kang Seo Joon is afraid he's hit rock bottom. But after a chance meeting brings the talented chef Han Ji Woo into his life, Seo Joon is certain his luck is about to change.

title: The Queen Who Crowns
synopsis: Queen Wongyeong from a powerful family marries Yi Bang-Won, helping him become King Taejong. But their relationship deteriorates when he takes concubines and diminishes her influence.

title: Hyper Knife
synopsis: A disgraced neurosurgeon performs illegal surgeries while confronting her dark past. When she meets her former mentor, a battle of power and revenge unfolds as she pushes ethical boundaries in pursuit of medical breakthroughs.

title: The Secret Romantic Guesthouse
synopsis: A work about an incident that takes place when the owners of the boarding house called 'Guest Summer Palace', which breaks stereotypes, and boarders with secrets gather to find Lee Seol who disappeared 13 years ago.

title: At A Distance, Spring Is Green
synopsis: A coming of age campus story about youth in their 20s whose lives appear to be like the beauty of spring from afar but cold and harsh when viewed up close.

title: Adamas
synopsis: A story of twin brothers uncovering the truth from an incident 22 years ago.

title: Come and Hug Me
synopsis: A dramatic drama depicting the love of a man and a woman whose lives are linked because of a murder since young age. Despite an unfortunate destiny and the stigma and pains, they will try to be happy and heal their wounds.

title: The Crowned Clown
synopsis: The story takes place in Joseon period, when power struggles surrounding the throne had reached extreme levels. In order to escape those who plan to assassinate him, the King puts a clown, who looks exactly like him, on the throne.

title: Imitation
synopsis: Based on the webtoon of the same name, it tells the story of the lives of idols in the entertainment industry, centered around the secret romance between a member of a rookie girl group and a member of the top boy group in the industry.

title: The Player 2: Master of Swindlers
synopsis: A money-stealing action drama in which the best players in each field, such as scammers, hackers, fighters, and drivers, band together to find and steal dirty money illegally collected by the rich.

title: Work Later, Drink Now
synopsis: The story of three women whose belief in life is one drink at the end of the day.

title: Second Shot at Love
synopsis: A woman in denial about her drinking problem encounters her former best friend from high school, now cold and unsympathetic. His changed attitude pushes her to investigate what altered him.

title: Search: WWW
synopsis: Three 21st century women, working at the top two competitive web portal companies, decide to put their careers ahead of everything else in their lives.

title: Branding in Seongsu
synopsis: After an accidental kiss causes a body swap, two ideologically opposed people struggle to navigate each other's lives.

title: Under the Queen's Umbrella
synopsis: Im Hwa Ryeong, a prickly, sensitive and hot-tempered queen, tries to turn her trouble making princes into proper crown princes.

title: Chief Detective 1958
synopsis: Park Young-Han (Lee Je-Hoon) is a young detective. He becomes furious at the reality of human dignity being violated and he struggles to deal with it. He teams up with his colleague detectives

title: Tree of Heaven
synopsis: Two soon-to-be step siblings grow close during their teen years, helping each other through family challenges. After high school, they part ways. Years later, they reunite alongside a cousin, rekindling unresolved emotions from their past.

title: High Society
synopsis: The youngest daughter of a chaebol family lives a simple life to hide her true identity as an heiress. She is in search of a man who will love her for who she is behind her wealth.

title: The Tyrant
synopsis: The story of people who gather to occupy samples for different purposes after the last sample of the so-called 'Tyrant Program' disappears in a delivery accident.

title: Crushology 101
synopsis: Bunny, a top sculpture student, struggles with self-esteem after a failed relationship. Her life changes when she meets Hwang Jae Yul, a warm design student, and Cha Ji Won, a perfect chaebol heir.

title: The Real Deal Has Come!
synopsis: Family drama begins to center around an unmarried pregnant woman and an unmarried man who enter into a false contract which leads to them to romance, pregnancy, childbirth, and childrearing.

title: The Scholar Who Walks the Night
synopsis: Jo Yang-sun disguises himself as a bookseller after the fall of his family. Meet Kim Sung-yeol, a vampire obsessed with his former love's double Choi Hye-ryung. The evil vampire Gwi conspires to deny the ascension of the Crown Prince.

title: House of Lies
synopsis: Ji-Na works as a contract employee, and appears to live a normal life. One day, she hears that her older sister Ji-Hyun is missing. Ji-Na goes to Rose Mansion Apartment, where unexpected events unfolds.

title: Low Life
synopsis: A fisherman as he discovers a treasure lost for generations at the bottom of the ocean. Taking a small part of it home for himself.

title: Run BTS!
synopsis: Run BTS (Dallyeola Bangtan!) is a South Korean show by the boy band BTS (Bangtan Sonyeondan). The show is all about BTS doing activities, challenges, games and lots more.

title: Captivating the King
synopsis: A work that deals with the cruel love story of King Yi In, who is in a political crisis, fighting for the throne, and Kang Hee-soo, a secret agent who approaches Yi In for revenge but ends up being enchanted.

title: Scent of a Woman
synopsis: Timid and considerate Yeon Jae finds out that she has only six months to live. She decides to quit her job and works hard to complete each dream in her bucket list.

title: SF8
synopsis: SF8 revolves around people who dream of a perfect society. It tackles the themes of artificial intelligence, augmented reality, virtual reality, robots, games, fantasy, horror, superpowers and disasters.

title: The Man Living in Our House
synopsis: A flight attendant returns to her hometown and visits her mother's grave. Later, she meets a young man who introduces himself to her as her mother's husband.

title: My Country: The New Age
synopsis: Set during the end of the Goryeo period to the early Joseon period. Two friends aim their swords against one another due to differences in opinion about "my country."

title: Queen of Ambition
synopsis: K-drama TV show about a young woman who becomes consumed by greed and ambition, and, the man who once loved her who's now determined to stop her and make her pay for her past sins.

title: Forecasting Love and Weather
synopsis: An office melodrama that depicts work life and love life of the people working in Korea Meteorological Administration which is hotter than tropical nights and more indispensable than local heavy rains.

title: Queen Woo
synopsis: A thrilling tale of Queen Woo, who, after the sudden death of the king, must marry one of the power-hungry princes to ensure her survival. A fierce battle in Goguryeo breaks out among the 5 tribes vying for the throne.

title: The Moon Embracing the Sun
synopsis: Set against the backdrop of a Korean traditional palace, this fantasy drama tells the poignant love story between a king and a female shaman.

title: The Master's Sun
synopsis: Tae Gong Sil has the ability to see ghosts, but their constant demands for help make her life impossible until she meets Joo Jong Won, a handsome CEO who measures everything by money, since when she touches him, the ghosts disappear.

title: Castaway Diva
synopsis: An aspiring singer who spends fifteen years alone on a deserted island before setting out on a journey to become a diva.

title: Doctor Stranger
synopsis: Park Hoon and his father were kidnapped by North Korea and he fell in love with Jae Hee, but lost contact.

title: Kill Me, Heal Me
synopsis: A love story between the son from a wealthy family who has 7 personalities Cha Do Hyun and Oh Ri Jin who becomes his secret psychiatrist.

title: Missing: The Other Side
synopsis: A village holds spirits of missing, deceased people. A search to find the missing bodies and discover the truth behind their disappearance occurs.

title: The Secret Life of My Secretary
synopsis: After Do Min Ik, a competent director, loses his ability to recognise faces, he becomes dependent on Jung Gal Hee, his secretary, and eventually develops feelings for her.

title: Behind Your Touch
synopsis: A veterinarian with psychic powers, and a hot-blooded detective who fall in love with each other while solving minor crime cases in a small town in Mujin, Chungcheong-do.

title: Omniscient Reader
synopsis: Dokja, an average office worker, finds his favorite web novel "Three Ways to Survive the Apocalypse" becoming reality. With unique knowledge of the impending doom, he strives to alter the story's fate and reshape his world.

title: Secret Love Affair
synopsis: A love story between a young poor student pianist and his older married piano teacher. Could their pure love for each other win, despite disapproval from the society and the "moral standard"?

title: Dr. Brain
synopsis: Brilliant brain scientist Sewon (Lee Sun-Kyun) suffers a horrific personal tragedy. Desperate to uncover what happened to his family, he conducts "brain syncs" with the dead to access their memories for clues.

title: Good Manager
synopsis: Chief Kim is an eccentric, flamboyant accountant genius working in the underground and trying to save up enough money to travel abroad until he accidentally gets employed by one of the most famous corporations in Korea.

title: Dong Yi
synopsis: Follows the story of a simple maid that rises high in the royal harem as a consort and, ultimately, mother of the Korean king.

title: Dragon Age: Absolution
synopsis: Set in the Tevinter Empire, the oldest of several human nations in Thedas explore the experiences of its different inhabitants.

title: Hi Bye, Mama!
synopsis: It's the story of a mother who died and begins a 49-day long project of reincarnation and a husband who has barely begun to live a new life after overcoming the pain of losing his wife.

title: A Love So Beautiful
synopsis: Love is as tough as it is sweet for a lovestruck teenager, whose relationship with her next-door neighbor transforms as they grow into adulthood.

title: Our Blooming Youth
synopsis: A story about a prince who receives a book about ghost stories containing all kinds of curses of life and feels that the curse is happening one by one

title: Seoul Busters
synopsis: The lowest-ranked squad in the county teams up with the leader of the elite Violent Crimes Team to transform into a top-performing squad.

title: Chief of Staff
synopsis: As a chief of staff in the National Assembly, Jang Tae-jun influences power behind the scenes while pursuing his own ambitions to rise to the top.

title: The Good Detective
synopsis: A drama about the race between people who want to get closer to the truth and those who want to cover it up.

title: Again My Life
synopsis: A hot-blooded prosecutor is murdered when he gets entangled in an investigation around a corrupt politician. He gets sent back in time to when he was 18 years old, and he prepares to take down his enemy.

title: Wok of Love
synopsis: Set at a small Chinese restaurant, "Wok of Love" follows Seo Poong's attempt at survival, food and love.

title: Rooftop Prince
synopsis: Crown Prince Lee Gak transports 300 years into the future following the death of his wife; in 21st century Seoul, he meets Joo Se-Na, a woman with an uncanny resemblance to the deceased princess.

title: Unlock My Boss
synopsis: The series is about a company president who gets trapped in a smartphone due to a suspicious incident, and an unemployed young man whose life changes after picking up the strange smartphone.

title: Dream High
synopsis: The story of six students at Kirin Art High School who work to achieve their dreams of becoming stars in the Korean music industry. Along the way, they discover the true meaning of friendship, love and life.

title: It's Okay, That's Love
synopsis: A love story between a psychiatrist named Ji Hae Soo and an author who had schizophrenia named Jang Jae Yeol.

title: Flower Crew: Joseon Marriage Agency
synopsis: A king makes a request to Joseon's best dating agency "Flower Crew" to protect his first love. Upon his request, the matchmakers at the agency risk their own lives to transform the lowly woman Gae Ddong into the most noble woman.

title: Like Flowers in Sand
synopsis: A delightful, lively human romantic comedy about the reunion of old wrestling prodigy Kim Baek-doo and old alley leader Oh Doo-sik, who are living in a tough present life.

title: Bad Guys
synopsis: Reinstated to eradicate the worst crimes in the city, a detective requests the release of three convicts to enlist their help in catching the felons still at large.

title: My Perfect Stranger
synopsis: A drama about a strange and beautiful time travel between a news anchor and an ordinary office worker trapped in 1987.

title: One Ordinary Day
synopsis: A remake of the BBC drama "Criminal Justice" that delves into the criminal justice system through the story of two men surrounding a woman's murder.

title: The Midnight Romance in Hagwon
synopsis: A secret and sweet real-life romance between veteran academy instructor Seo Hye-jin and her flirty student Lee Joon-ho, who returns after 10 years and stirs her heart.

title: Mystic Pop-up Bar
synopsis: A young man with an unique ability begins working for a centuries-old bar owner who resolves her customers' emotional troubles by entering their dreams.

title: Son: The Guest
synopsis: A psychic, a Catholic priest, and a detective team up to fight crimes caused by supernatural forces.

title: You Are Beautiful
synopsis: Go Mi-Nyu, a girl about to become a nun, is asked to cover for her indisposed twin brother, Mi-Nam, who's on the verge of becoming a k-idol. To do so, she disguises herself as a boy and joins A.N.Jell, a really popular boy band.

title: Marie and Her Three Daddies
synopsis: Ma-Ri is linked to three men who might be her biological father. They fight, compete, then learn to parent together. Misunderstandings cause chaos, then resolution and in the end they learn what "family" means beyond blood.

title: Class of Lies
synopsis: A highly successful lawyer falls from grace because of one case. He becomes a fixed term teacher at a high school. Though he goes into the classroom for selfish reasons, he begins to see the crimes and takes matters into his own hands.

title: Mine
synopsis: Encaged in a gold-clad life of secrets and lies, two women in a conglomerate family seek to topple all that stands in their way of finding true joy.

title: I Kill U
synopsis: Seon U comes from a poor family background. She was once a promising Taekwondo athlete, but she now works part-time jobs to support herself. One day, she is selected to become the stand-in for Ji Yeon due to their similar appearance. Ji Yeon is the granddaughter of Beomhan Construction Company's chairman. She was the driver of a fatal hit-and-run car accident. Seon U must play Ji Yeon in front of the public and media. Meanwhile, Seon U becomes the target of Ho Jung's hostility. Ho Jung is Ji Yeon's stepbrother, and he has an inferiority complex over Ji Yeon. He wants to become the successor to Beomhan Construction Company.

title: Cheese in the Trap
synopsis: A college student balances her studies and a part-time job with a relationship with an insecure man who manipulates others.

title: Where Stars Land
synopsis: Two people overcome ups and downs in their lives to find true romance and make dreams come true at Incheon International Airport.

title: Chicken Nugget
synopsis: A woman steps into an odd machine and becomes - a chicken nugget? Now, it's up to her father and admirer to embark on a zany quest to bring her back.

title: Hyena
synopsis: 'Hyena' deals with very competitive, private lawyers who only work for the richest 1% of society.

title: Emperor of the Sea
synopsis: Jang Bo Go, a Shilla slave sold to China during Tang Dynasty, trains as a gladiator-slave. Overcoming adversity, he returns home and becomes a successful sea merchant battling pirates plaguing maritime trade routes.

title: BTS: Bon Voyage
synopsis: BTS: Bon Voyage is a reality show about members of South Korean boy band BTS (Bangtan Sonyeondan) travelling. It shows them in everyday situations that every traveller encounters and offers an unique insight in members' lives.

title: Remarriage & Desires
synopsis: Through an exclusive matchmaking agency, women strive to marry a desirable bachelor and into the highest echelon of society.

title: Another Miss Oh
synopsis: A romantic television series about two women who not only share the same name Oh Hae Young but they also share a destiny with the same man, Park Do Kyung, who can see the future.

title: Serendipity's Embrace
synopsis: Animation producer Lee reunites with Hu, her high school heartbreak, a decade later. As old feelings resurface, can they give love another chance or have they drifted too far apart?

title: Money Heist: Korea - Joint Economic Area
synopsis: A genius strategist and people with different personalities and abilities fighting an extraordinary variable and engaging in an unprecedented hostage play.

title: The Great Doctor
synopsis: When the queen-to-be of medieval Korea is badly wounded, Captain Choi Young uses a wormhole to "heaven," which is actually 21st-century South Korea, to bring back the spoiled Dr. Yoo Eun-Soo who becomes a pawn in a game of human chess.

title: Spring of Youth
synopsis: When a K-pop star's band kicks him out, he enrolls in college and falls for a music student, who might be the key to his next musical venture.

title: Why Her
synopsis: Oh Soo-jae is a talented lawyer and the youngest partner at TK Law Firm, the best law firm in South Korea. She gets involved in an unexpected case and she gets demoted to work as an adjunct professor at a law school.

title: Love in Sadness
synopsis: When Yoon Ma-ri continuously suffers abuse from Kang In-wook, she has Seo Jung-won, a plastic surgeon, perform surgery on her so that she can start a new life.

title: Joseon Attorney
synopsis: A fusion historical drama that combines romance and legal heroes, and contains a fictional story based on the motif of Gyeongguk Daejeon.

title: The Cursed
synopsis: "The Cursed" is about a teenage girl who has the ability to bring death by using names, photos, and belongings, and a just social issues reporter, fighting against the massive evil hidden behind an IT conglomerate.

title: Warrior Baek Dong Soo
synopsis: Childhood friends Baek Dong Soo and Yeo Woon are both prodigies in combat. But while Baek Dong Soo became the top swordsman in the land, Yeo Woon would go on to serve a group of clandestine assassins whose aim is to overthrow the throne.

title: Marriage Contract
synopsis: A poor, widowed woman, desperate to support her 7-year-old daughter, and a wealthy business executive with a sick mother enter into a contract marriage together.

title: 365: Repeat the Year
synopsis: A story where ten people get the chance to go back in time by one year, but unexpectedly mysterious situations start to arise when their fates are changed and twisted in the process.

title: No Secret
synopsis: A well-respected announcer suddenly loses his ability to self-censor on air, catching the attention of a TV writer who invites him on her variety show.

title: Moon in the Day
synopsis: A dangerous and affectionate romance between a man whose time stops after being killed by his beloved lover and a woman who loses her memory of her previous life and whose time passes away endlessly.

title: In the SOOP BTS Ver.
synopsis: The members of BTS enjoy the beauty of the SOOP as they create their own schedules in advance and each spend time enjoying their hobbies. From painting to canoeing, the seven of them will be spending time together in the same place.

title: Life on Mars
synopsis: While investigating a serial murder case, Han Tae Joo gets into an incident. When he wakes up, he finds himself back in 1987. To get back to his present world, he must solve the murder case.

title: Dark Hole
synopsis: About a group of survivors who have to fight for their lives against mutants that are created when humans breathe mysterious dark smoke from a sinkhole.

title: Princess Hours
synopsis: Love, tradition, and politics collide when a spirited young art student is betrothed to the crown prince of South Korea.

title: A Virtuous Business
synopsis: Four women started selling adult products door-to-door in a rural village in 1992, a time when "sex" was still taboo.

title: The Fabulous
synopsis: Four best friends chase their dreams alongside the fashion elite while juggling demanding jobs, romantic dilemmas, and wild nights on the town.

title: Hi Cookie
synopsis: A drama about what happens when a dangerous handmade cookie that fulfills a dream devours an elite high school.

title: Sungkyunkwan Scandal
synopsis: In the Joseon era, Kim Yoon-hee masquerades as a boy to earn a living as a book transcriber. Her family's dire circumstances and the encouragement of a noble's son finally drive her to attend Sungkyukwan University, forbidden for females.

title: Check-in Hanyang
synopsis: Yongcheonru is the grandest guesthouse in Joseon. Their motto is that the customer is the king. Yeongcheonru has four new interns and they have their own reasons why they work there.

title: Life
synopsis: A medical drama that depicts the power struggles and human stories that take place within a university hospital.

title: Reply 1994
synopsis: In 1994, college students were crazy about basketball and Korea's hip-hop artists; with students from various countryside areas attending college in Seoul, they mingle together for true friendship, love and lots of fun at a boarding house.

title: Unintentional Love Story
synopsis: Ji Won Young's supervisor is fired for corruption and, although he is innocent of any wrongdoing, he is also fired. To get his job back, he tries to ingratiate himself with the president by seeking out his favorite artist.

title: More Than Friends
synopsis: A romantic drama about a man and a woman who, due to a misunderstanding, have held a crush on each other for over 10 years.

title: My Roommate Is a Gumiho
synopsis: The thrilling love story of Shin Woo Yeo, a 999-years-old gumiho who wants to become human, and Lee Dam, who accidentally swallowed his fox bead.

title: Something About 1%
synopsis: A kind school teacher suddenly becomes heir to a large company on the condition she marries the owner's grandson. As she is interested in neither, they make a deal that if they manage to date for a full six months, he will inherit instead.

title: KBS Drama Special
synopsis: A weekly program on KBS2 showing short dramas, with each episode having a different story, cast, director, and writer.

title: Love Is for Suckers
synopsis: Goo Yeo Reum, is producing a dating-themed reality TV show called "Kingdom of Love". Her neighbour and best friend, Park Jae Hoon, a plastic surgeon, agrees to become a contestant, and the two begin developing romantic feelings.

title: The School Nurse Files
synopsis: Wielding a light-up sword through the dark corners of a high school, a nurse with an unusual gift protects students from monsters only she can see.

title: Agency
synopsis: It follows a woman who became the first female executive in her group to make her way to the highest position.

title: The Emperor: Owner of the Mask
synopsis: Crown Prince Lee Sun battles Pyunsoo hwe, an oppressive 18th-century Joseon group, helping civilians during water scarcity caused by privatization. Ga-eun aids him in overcoming obstacles to become a just ruler.

title: Kairos
synopsis: A fantasy thriller about a man who is in shock of losing his daughter and a woman who lives in the past, both struggling to save the ones they love.

title: SKZ Code
synopsis: Reality show web series by South Korean boy group Stray Kids. It features the group taking part in different games and activities.

title: Once Again
synopsis: A story about love and family based on the Song Family, who never have a peaceful day.

title: My Only Love Song
synopsis: When things don't go her way during a shooting for her new show, a top actress runs away in an old van that guides her on a time-traveling journey.

title: Queenmaker
synopsis: An accomplished fixer for a powerful business conglomerate jumps into politics to make a headstrong civil rights lawyer the next mayor of Seoul.

title: A Bloody Lucky Day
synopsis: An ordinary taxi driver who becomes entangled with a customer that turns out to be a serial killer.

title: Tale of the Nine Tailed: An Unfinished Story
synopsis: The 3 episode spinoff will tell the story of Lee Rang and Ki Yoo Ri before and during the events of Tale of the Nine Tailed (2020).

title: To My Haeri
synopsis: A healing romance about a woman, Hae-ri, who developed dissociative personality disorder due to the disappearance of her sister and the grief caused by the break-up with her longtime lover, Hyeon-oh.

title: The Last Empress
synopsis: In an alternate universe where Korea is a monarchy, an actress marries the emperor. As time passes, she gets caught up in a power struggle and the investigation of a murder that threatens the regime.

title: Hush
synopsis: A sympathetic and humane office drama based in a newspaper company, about the dilemma between the survival and conscience of reporters.

title: Live On
synopsis: The story of Baek Ho Rang who joins the broadcasting club of her high school, led by Go Eun Taek, in order to find out who is the person trying to reveal her secret.

title: Divorce Attorney Shin
synopsis: Driven by a personal tragedy, a pianist-turned-lawyer navigates the complex world of divorce - fighting for his clients to win by any means necessary.

title: Dinner Mate
synopsis: A man and woman waiting at a restaurant are mistaken for a couple and decide to have dinner together.

title: Date My Friend
synopsis: Top Korean celebrities play matchmaker for friends who are great catches but unlucky in love-or just haven't met the right one yet. Will they open up and fall in love?

title: The Rebel Hong Gil Dong
synopsis: Story of Hong Gil Dong, often said to be Robin Hood of Korea during Joseon Dynasty.

title: The Wind Blows
synopsis: A story about a man who decided to divorce his beloved wife after suffering from Alzheimer's disease and a woman who decided to divorce her husband to have children. The plot unfolds six years later when they reunite.

title: Live
synopsis: The drama revolves around the incidents that occur among the police force and the joy, sorrow, and pain that police officers experience as they try to protect justice.

title: Queen In-hyun's Man
synopsis: Kim Boong Do is a scholar who travels 300 years into the future of modern Seoul and meets Choi Hee Jin, a no-name actress who is expecting a career renaissance through her role as Queen In Hyun in a TV drama.

title: Psychopath Diary
synopsis: "Psychopath Diary" is the story of Yook Dong Sik who coincidentally picks up the diary of a serial killer.

title: Chimera
synopsis: An explosion took place in the past. That explosion led to a serial murder case known as the Chimera case. 35 years later, a similar explosion takes place.

title: The Lady in Dignity
synopsis: The story of an elegant Cheongdam-dong woman named Woo Ah Jin, who relished a life of luxury by marrying a quasi-chaebol son, until Park Bok Ja walks into her life.

title: Chicago Typewriter
synopsis: Writers that lived under Japanese rule in the 1930s are reincarnated into a bestselling writer who is in a slump, a mysterious ghostwriter, and a devoted fan of the bestselling writer.

title: Dongjae, the Good or the Bastard
synopsis: A lawyer Seo Dongjae takes on the murder case of a high school girl and is conflicted between his intuition as a prosecutor and his instinct as an opportunist.

title: Nobody Knows
synopsis: Still haunted by the death of her friend who was murdered 19 years ago by the infamous Stigmata serial killer, detective Cha Young Jin is determined to catch the culprit.

title: My Name Is Gabriel
synopsis: The life of another person will start now. For 72 hours, live the actual lives of strangers.

title: Boyfriend on Demand

She considers money the most valuable thing in the world - which makes her single-minded in the pursuit of prospective son-in-laws. Her own marriage experience was unhappy, so she's set on making sure it's different for her children. She marries off the elder daughter to a doctor, then turns her attention to the younger daughter, Hye Yoon (Jung So Min) but only to have the daughter reveal that she wants marry to an ordinary salary man, Jung Hoon (Sung Joon).

She remarried, and when her second husband died 5 years later, she brought up her two young stepdaughters like her own. She was against the marriage when her youngest stepdaughter Oh Yeong Chae wanted to marry Kim Hyeon Tae, a rookie boxer and an orphan, but she relented. When Yeong Chae, who was involved in a hit-and-run accident, died after giving birth to a son, Jin Sook blamed and hated her son-in-law. After Yeong Chae's death, Hyeon Tae and his son stayed together with Jin Sook and treated her like his mother. When she saw how Hyeon Tae took care of his son, her attitude towards him changed. Now she treats Hyeon Tae like her real son. One day, Hyeon Tae falls in love with a woman named Park Soo Kyeong. Jin Sook, who is unhappy with Soo Kyeong, finds out that Soo Kyeong is her real daughter. Although she is eager to reunite with Soo Kyeong, she is in a dilemma as Soo Kyeong hates her birth mother for abandoning her. Hyeon Tae finally marries Soo Kyeong, but it also causes conflicts.

A young boy from Earth, Tony Jones, is summoned into the Moonlands as he is believed to be this Final Dreamer. He joins forces with the apprentice Magi, Edyn, and the Shadow Stalker, Strag, on a mission to gather the Dreamstones before Agram is set free. Using the Book of Elders, the three travel through the Moonlands while combating the forces of Agram and gaining an ever-growing collection of Dream Creatures from the Moonlands that they visit.
